import scala.math._

val n = 1000

def nd(x: Double) = {
    ((1 / pow(2 * Pi, 0.5)) * exp(-pow(x, 2)/2))
}
val p = (-n to n).map(i => nd(i / 200.0)).toList
var sum = 0.0
val dfv = p.map(pi => {sum += (pi / 200.0); sum})

import scala.util.Random
val r = new Random

val (a, b) = (0.0, 200.0)

val res: List[Double] = (0 until 1000).map(i => {val f = r.nextFloat; val jk = dfv.count(_ <= f).toDouble * (b - a) / 2000 + a; println(f + " " + dfv.count(_ <= f)); jk}).toList

import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
import org.apache.spark.sql.Row

val df = spark.createDataFrame(
    spark.sparkContext.parallelize(res).map(t => Row(t)), 
    StructType(
        Seq(
            StructField("value", DataTypes.DoubleType, false)
            )
    )
)

z.show(df.groupBy('value).count)
